text.text: To influence Mount Sinai Health System’s reputation, the Social Media Department has trained physicians from each U.S. News and World Report ranked service line to be brand ambassadors on either Twitter, LinkedIn, or Instagram. This initiative has enabled physicians to build further awareness and to improve reputational scores across Mount Sinai’s ranked specialties. Physicians are responsible for managing their own social media accounts with support from the Health System.​

text.text:
Back the Front Line | #MountSinaiStrong

Mount Sinai launched innovative programs using its social footprint to raise funds early on in the COVID crisis. Broadway performers helped by providing Songs for Mount Sinai videos. Each influencer, celebrity and partner got a unique flow code and URL, directing users to the donations page. With hefty reach and engagement, it raised $1.6 million through social media.
